<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="449" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,700,151,213]" box="[151,245,187,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">
<figureCitation box="[151,245,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,849,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-321@6.[151,1435,849,1842]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Scotiazoa lilium. A colony, scale bar = 1cm; B, larva; C, zooid." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5074607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5074607/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">Figure 6</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,259,826]" box="[151,782,259,286]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">Stations: Kanadeep CP 5095; CP 5109. Nine specimens.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,259,826]" box="[151,741,295,322]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">
<taxonomicName authority="Monniot C. &amp; Monniot F. 1982" authorityName="Monniot C. &amp; Monniot F." authorityYear="1982" box="[151,737,295,322]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Holozoidae" genus="Protoholozoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lilium">
<emphasis box="[151,375,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">Protoholozoa lilium</emphasis>
Monniot C. &amp; Monniot F. 1982
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,259,826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">
All colonies are brittle, very soft with a triangular head above a long cylindrical peduncle (
<figureCitation box="[1152,1241,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,849,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-321@6.[151,1435,849,1842]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Scotiazoa lilium. A colony, scale bar = 1cm; B, larva; C, zooid." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5074607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5074607/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). The diameter of the head (always damaged) is about 
<quantity box="[553,604,367,393]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" unit="cm" value="1.0">1cm</quantity>
, the longest peduncle is 
<quantity box="[874,928,367,394]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" unit="cm" value="6.0">6 cm</quantity>
with 
<quantity box="[990,1054,367,394]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
in diameter. The zooids have their thorax and abdomen contained in the transparent tunic of the head the post abdominal vascular extensions extend into the peduncle. The thorax is in vertical position for most of the zooids with the atrial aperture at the top surface of the colony and the oral siphon near the peduncle. The thoraces are narrow 
<quantity box="[982,1097,475,502]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" unit="mm" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6 to 8 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation box="[1168,1256,475,502]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,849,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-321@6.[151,1435,849,1842]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Scotiazoa lilium. A colony, scale bar = 1cm; B, larva; C, zooid." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5074607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5074607/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). The body wall is thin with circular muscles at the base of the oral siphon and with 15 transverse muscles along the thorax. There are eight to ten oral tentacles. The branchial tissue includes three transverse bars on each side attached to the endostyle and a dorsal membrane. This organisation corresponds to that of specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1119,1293,583,610]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
described as 
<taxonomicName box="[151,374,619,645]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Holozoidae" genus="Protoholozoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lilium">
<emphasis box="[151,374,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">Protoholozoa lilium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Monniot, C. &amp; Monniot, F." box="[416,717,619,645]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" pagination="357 - 448" refId="ref9884" refString="Monniot, C. &amp; Monniot, F. (1991) Tunicata: peuplements d'ascidies profondes en Nouvelle Caledonie. Diversite des strategies adaptatives. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle Paris, A, 151, 357 - 448." type="journal article" year="1991">Monniot &amp; Monniot (1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[729,811,619,646]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1448,1472]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,915,1424]" captionTargetId="figure-273@15.[151,1435,915,1424]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 15. Pyura viarecta. A, body ventrally opened; B, same body, branchial sac removed. Scale bars = 1cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5074629" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5074629/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). The digestive loop encircles the hermaphrodite gonad. The ovary is anterior to the testis vesicles which are arranged in a rosette. A pedunculate brood pouch (
<figureCitation box="[1315,1402,655,682]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,849,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-321@6.[151,1435,849,1842]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Scotiazoa lilium. A colony, scale bar = 1cm; B, larva; C, zooid." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5074607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5074607/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
) is inserted at the base of the thorax and occasionally contains a single larva. The tadpole has three adhesive papillae in a triangle and one otolith (
<figureCitation box="[446,535,727,754]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,849,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-321@6.[151,1435,849,1842]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Scotiazoa lilium. A colony, scale bar = 1cm; B, larva; C, zooid." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5074607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5074607/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
). The larval body is 
<quantity box="[764,850,727,754]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
long encircled by the tail.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,259,826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">
The structure of the larva is typical of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berrill" authorityYear="1950" box="[683,812,763,789]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Holozoidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Holozoidae</taxonomicName>
family. It confirms the attribution of the species to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F.Monniot &amp; Tatian" authorityYear="2020" box="[224,333,799,825]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Holozoidae" genus="Scotiazoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[224,333,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">Scotiazoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
instead of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kott" authorityYear="1969" box="[456,607,799,825]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Holozoidae" genus="Protoholozoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[456,607,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">Protoholozoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Monniot, F. &amp; Tatian, M." box="[667,936,799,825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" pagination="261 - 268" refId="ref10114" refString="Monniot, F. &amp; Tatian, M. (2020) Questions on the taxonomic status of species of Protoholozoa Kott, 1969 (Ascidiacea, Aplousobranchia, Holozoidae) with a description of a new genus. Zootaxa, 4718 (2), 261 - 268. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4718.2.7." type="journal article" year="2020">Monniot &amp; Tatian 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
